article.description: Jack Crook scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds to help lead Seattle University to a 61-52 win over Eastern Washington on Monday night.
article.headline: Seattle University clips Eastern Washington, 61-52
article.story: SEATTLE -- Jack Crook scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds to help lead Seattle University to a 58-52 win over Eastern Washington on Monday night. After Eastern Washington's Bogdan Bliznyuk drilled a 3-pointer to tie the game at 52 with 2:57 left, the Redhawks (1-3) closed the game on a 9-0 run to seal it. Crook scored the first four points of the run, making a 3-pointer followed by a 1 of 2 trip to the free throw line. Aaron Menzies hit a 3-pointer with 25 seconds left and Malik Montoya added the exclamation point with a layup 12 seconds later. Menzies, along with Brendan Westendorf, William Powell, and Jadon Cohee each had 10 points for Seattle. Venky Jois led Eastern Washington (2-2) with 14 points and eight rebounds. This was the second meeting in five days between the schools. Eastern Washington beat Seattle 76-70 on Wednesday.
